There was more drama off-the-pitch than in the field of play. Mamelodi Sundowns and Orlando Pirates' PSL clash at Loftus Stadium on Saturday, which was the pick of the weekend, is still the subject of debate this week. From an hour before kick-off of this clash that ended goalless, Pirates and Downs officials were already at loggerheads when the Bucs bus was about to enter the stadium. Then followed a Sundowns supporters who wanted to attack Pirates assistant coach Rhulani Mokwena on the touchline, but the fire was doused before it went far. Here's the whole drama in pictures: 